import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['population'], color='c')
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across the states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Population'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='engineers', ascending=False)
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='state', y='engineers', legend=False, figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engineers across the states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Engineers')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_hurricanes = data.groupby('Year')['Hurricanes'].sum()
    yearly_hurricanes.plot(kind='line', legend=True, label='Hurricanes')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of hurricanes across the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
